strings.Value: "Of course, you haven't always been easy to tolerate, but I'm glad we reached the end of this adventure together."
"Well, it's time to get to work. To ask, as you put it, that we be left alone."

{n}Jubilost shifts from one foot to the other, either from anxiety or impatience.{/n} "I look around and I think â€” should we really have been so eager to get to {g|First World}the First World{/g}? I suppose it's time we ask that he leave our lands alone and take himself back where he comes from..."

"Jubilost Narthropple, the most unbearable researcher of {g|Golarion}Golarion{/g}, at your service!" {n}Jubilost makes a curt bow, then scratches the back of his head and sighs.{/n} "We've seen a lot together. I hope you've said that for a reason, and the good memories outweigh the bad ones just a little bit!"

"Of course! I never became the hero who saved the entire gnome race! I don't even know how I'll live with myself, knowing that I'm just a famous scientist who visited the {g|First World}First World{/g}, met one of its deities, and defeated another. Assuming we win this battle."
"We'll ask them all right! Who can say no to politeness and forcible, explosive arguments?"
